post_text:
The much anticipated Back to School Plan for 2020-2021 is now available on our District Webpage: http://mitchelltigers.org/returntolearn.html or mitchelltigers.org > Return to School Guide (left side)

Teachers and Staff are extremely excited to see students again! While daily life will be a little different than in years prior, we are committed to providing the best education in the safest environment possible. To cut to the chase: We plan to start on August 13th as originally scheduled and the chart will show you the precautions we will have in place.

Please take a moment to review the information. Please CALL or EMAIL Dr. Urbanek, Mr. Peters, Mr. Kuxhausen or Mrs. Splichal with questions. We ask for your patience and kindness as we work through this very unique start of the school year. Go Tigers!

Tiger News:
Beginning July 1st, the Governor has removed all restrictions on contact sports (football, basketball, soccer, wrestling, and cheerleading) The NSAA will expect all member schools to follow our summer bylaws, including any directed health measure that is put into place by the Governor. Camps and clinics are permissible. Social distancing should be encouraged at all times when possible. Please have a detailed plan in place to clean/disinfect and continue to work with your local heath partners.
If there are further guidelines released from the Governor’s office or CDC, the NSAA will advise accordingly.

Go Tigers!

Beginning June 18th NSAA member schools are permitted to participate in camps, clinics, and summer leagues in all NSAA sanctioned activities except basketball, football, soccer, and wrestling.
Effective immediately NSAA member schools may hold open gyms for basketball, football, soccer, and wrestling with the following restrictions:

Individual skills and workouts only

No physical contact with others

No sharing of equipment

No grouping of students

post_text:
Calibraska Art Initiative Summer Program
MHS alumni Erica Larsen-Dockray (99') is the Founding Director of the Calibraska Arts Initiative and is offering a variety of online summer classes in the arts taught by teaching artists and professionals in Los Angeles, CA and beyond. We think these are really great opportunities for our students and parents (there are adult classes too!).

Classes start June 15th and run through July 31st. Registration closes the Wednesday before the start of each class so definitely have a look sooner than later if you can. There are scholarships in the form of 25%, 50%, and 100% available as well as class material kits available for anyone needing extra help or who may be interested in a series of classes. Check out all the great classes by visiting www.calibraska.org

GO TIGERS!

post_text:
I’m sure most of you have seen the recent updates--National, state, and local officials are strongly urging everyone to focus on social distancing and your personal health--mental and physical. We encourage you to keep doing all those recommendations--wash your hands often, disinfect, stay home as much as possible, and wear a cloth mask when you are out in public. Officials encourage limiting essential shopping to only once a week with one person doing the shopping.

It’s safe to say we expect more cases to be announced in our area, but there are people that have recovered and are doing well. That’s encouraging news in a time when we need some positive vibes!

Teachers will be expecting students to remain engaged in alternative learning through Thursday, but we encourage a break for the long Easter Weekend. We would have been out of school Friday and Monday, so we will also be out of alternative learning those days. Teachers will be back to working with your students on Tuesday, April 14th!

shared_text:
Morrill-Mitchell FFA and Agriculture Department
April 3 at 4:24 PM ·

Congratulations to our State FFA Degree recipients today.

We were supposed to be in Lincoln, watching you walk across the stage to receive your degree and charm. While we feel the heartache and disappointment, we have to remember that our time in the blue jacket lives on after our accomplishments.

We are so proud of each of you for dedicating your time, energy, passion and knowledge to our chapter for the last 4 years.

I wish we could be together today, but we WILL honor you as soon as we are able to. I can't wait to add your hand prints to the wall of the ag room and to the growing list of State FFA Degree's from our chapter.

Congratulations to;
Laura Sherrod
Teagan Flick
Russell Schaefer
Rylie Mason
Jonathan Pieper
Corbin Batt
Shandie Hess
Regan Hodsden
Kaden Bradley (not pictured)

**Photo Credits to Jenny Batt**

Tiger News: All remaining NSAA activity practices and competitions, including district and state competitions, have been cancelled for this school year. These cancellations are part of a new Directed Health Measure issued by Governor Ricketts.

Bylaw 3.2.7 (Summer Activities) will go into effect on May 26th. In the interim, Bylaw 3.2.6.1 (School-Year, Out-of-Season) is expected to be followed by all member school athletic programs.

The NSAA continues to encourage all member schools to follow CDC, local, state and federal health department recommendations.

The May 1st Transfer List deadline remains unchanged.

Any further official updates will be posted on the NSAA website and the NSAA social media platforms.

The NSAA is aware of the fluidity of COVID-19 and the potential impact hosting statewide events could have regarding the on-going public health threat. Many of our member schools are making decisions in the best interest of their student participants, coaches and communities. The NSAA is regretfully suspending district and state speech contests until further notice.

This is an unprecedented event. The NSAA Board of Directors and staff understand the hardship this has created for our membership. The NSAA will use this time to evaluate potential alternatives and the next steps for moving forward.

Sincerely,

Jeff Stauss

The Mitchell One-Acts team had 8 actors receive top honors, being recognized for Outstanding Performance at their district competition Friday, November 6th - Lexie Funk, Anyssa Lopez, Kaylinn Harimon, Alicia Sanchez, Lexie Jackson, Dylan Gardner and John Plasencio (not pictured Eric Wilson). As a team, the performance received a judges ranking of Superior.

In addition to the district awards, Lexie Funk, Lexie Jackson and John Plasencio also received WTC honors of Supporting Actor/Actress and Alicia Sanchez received the award of Western Trails Conference Outstanding Actress for her portrayal of Hannah in Lafayette No. 1

Mitchell Cross Country Teams Qualify For STATE!
Both Girls and Boys Cross Country teams ran to Runner-Up finishes in the team standings at the District Meet in Ogallala on October 17.
In the Girls Division, Regan Hodsden finished in 4th position and Lilian Golden finished in 6th!
In the Boys Division, Ashtyn Martin finished 5th, Caden Knutson finished 6th and Josiah Anaya finished 15th!

The following student athletes will be competing at the State Meet in Kearney on Friday, October 25!

Regan Hodsden (12), 20:26.3

Congratulations!

GO TIGERS!

Mitchell HS Fine Arts Booster Club invites everyone and anyone to come out and spend a few hours keeping Nebraska beautiful by picking up trash for a cause! This benefits the Fine Arts groups at Mitchell High School.
We will meet at the Mitchell HS on Sunday October 20th at 1pm and head out on site from there. Trash bags and vests will be supplied. Please bring gloves and wear appropriate shoes and outer wear as we will be walking.

*any HS student that needs community services hours, Fine Arts students and parents, and just anyone wanting to come out and help are welcome!
See you there and GO TIGERS!

~~Please follow the Mitchell High School Fine Arts Booster Club on Facebook for all events, updates and happenings!~~
